    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1774" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄχνυμαι</span></b>  (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀχ</span>), ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄχνυτο</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be distressed, grieve;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινός</span>, ‘for’ some one; often w. acc.
          of specification (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κῆρ</span>); also <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κῆρ ἄχνυται, ἄχνυται θῡμὸς ἐνὶ στήθεσσιν ἐμοῖσιν, Ξ
            38</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 14.170</span></i>. Cf.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀκαχίζω</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
